# Commit Conventions

Full reference: `docs/commit-conventions.md`

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `test`, `refactor`, `perf`, `chore`, `style`, `build`, `ci`

Scopes: `domain`, `application`, `data`, `ui`, `i18n`, `docs`, `cursor`, `sync`, `parser`

## Rules

- All commit messages and PR titles **must be in English**
- Subject: imperative mood, max 72 chars, no period
- Reference use cases and business rules in body: `Refs: UC-004`, `Refs: BR-007`
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit secrets, keystores, `local.properties`, or build artifacts
- Never commit unless the user explicitly asks

## Before committing code changes

- Domain layer changes require unit tests first (TDD)
- New user flows require documented use case in `docs/use-cases/`
- New domain terms must match `docs/glossary.md`
- UI strings via i18n keys only

## PR description template

```markdown
## Summary
## Use cases
## Test plan
```
